Consider this:

```json
{
  "mark": {"type": "point"},
  "encoding": {
    "opacity": {
      "field": "x",
      "scale": {"range": {"field": "o"}},
      "type": "nominal"
    }
  },
  "transform": [{"calculate": "if(datum.x,0.5,1)", "as": "o"}],
  "data": {"values": [{"x": false}, {"x": true}]}
}
```

This [works](https://vega.github.io/editor/#/url/vega-lite/N4IgtghgTg1iBcoAuBPADgUwSNB7AlgHZIgC+ANCBoQMa4AmRA5gqLmhDfqqyAGb4MAG3rYAHiEoBnGhCFZEIKBEJMFoAcNHwQuMhRCpM2QrjBE5+ykmWEpfXFDAIA2qFlCaAVyEQkCkHw+AAp6Py8wADoxcgAGSIBWcgBGAEpJEAgpbD1SAF1KMKQIXgA3OS8MbPg3EAl4PjkpDApQeptK-NJSIA) perfectly fine:

![visualization(144)](https://github.com/vega/vega-lite/assets/866859/fcdeecfb-40c5-451a-aa85-83adc705fa3e)

So far so good.

But then watch [what happens](https://vega.github.io/editor/#/url/vega-lite/N4IgtghgTg1iBcoAuBPADgUwSNB7AlgHZIgC+ANCBoQMa4AmRA5gqLmhDfqqyAGb4MAG3rYAHiEoBnGhCFZEIKBEJMFoAcNHwQuMhRCpM2QrjBE5+ykmWEpfXFDAIA2qFlCaAVyEQkCkHw+AAp6Py8wADoxcgAGSIBWcgBGAEpJEAgpbD1SAF1KMKQIXgA3OS8MbPg3EAl4PjkpDApQesahZvzSUiA) if I change `true` for `false` (or vice-versa):

```json
{
  "mark": {"type": "point"},
  "encoding": {
    "opacity": {
      "field": "x",
      "scale": {"range": {"field": "o"}},
      "type": "nominal"
    }
  },
  "transform": [{"calculate": "if(datum.x,0.5,1)", "as": "o"}],
  "data": {"values": [{"x": false}, {"x": false}]}
}
```
![visualization(145)](https://github.com/vega/vega-lite/assets/866859/d27a4db4-f230-4ada-95b4-6a036dfe4b38)

Oops.

A similar problem occurs if I [change](https://vega.github.io/editor/#/url/vega-lite/N4IgtghgTg1iBcoAuBPADgUwSNB7AlgHZIgC+ANCBoQMa4AmRA5gqLmhDfqqyAGb4MAG3rYAHiEoBnGhCFZEIKBEJMFoAcNHwQuMhRCpM2QrjBE5+ykmWEpfXFDAIA2qFlCaAVyEQkCkABGSRAIKWw9UgBdSno-CF4ANzkvDHD4NxAJeD45KQwKUGybVOjSUiA) the expression to just return a constant:

```json
{
  "mark": {"type": "point"},
  "encoding": {
    "opacity": {
      "field": "x",
      "scale": {"range": {"field": "o"}},
      "type": "nominal"
    }
  },
  "transform": [{"calculate": "1", "as": "o"}],
  "data": {"values": [{"x": false}, {"x": true}]}
}
```
![visualization(146)](https://github.com/vega/vega-lite/assets/866859/2b55226d-6d2c-4563-9463-73b192df2cd6)

The issue can be seen in-browser and in the PNG exports above. However, somewhat mindbogglingly, SVG exports don't show the problem?!

![visualization(4)](https://github.com/vega/vega-lite/assets/866859/6ec94112-3c9c-4c5d-9974-1da547a7c7b9)

It's also worth noting that while `opacity` is affected, `color` [isn't](https://vega.github.io/editor/#/url/vega-lite/N4IgtghgTg1iBcoAuBPADgUwSNB7AlgHZIgC+ANCBoQMa4AmRA5gqHQDa5SsgBm+GdvWwAPEJQDONCOyyIQUCISZzQ-QcPggaZCiFSZshXGCIzdlJIsITeXMAgDabGTQCu7CEjkh8vABT0Xm5gAHQi5ADkTFAY1JFRsfSRAJTiIBAS2DqkALqUQUgQPABuMm4YWfDOIGLwvDISGBSgdQ3sTXmkpEA):

```json
{
  "mark": {"type": "point"},
  "encoding": {
    "color": {
      "field": "x",
      "scale": {"range": {"field": "c"}},
      "type": "nominal"
    }
  },
  "transform": [{"calculate": "if(datum.x,'green','red')", "as": "c"}],
  "data": {"values": [{"x": false}, {"x": false}]}
}
```
![visualization(147)](https://github.com/vega/vega-lite/assets/866859/1707a3e4-126d-499e-8855-452cc7f1e515)

comment.body:
One workaround is to stop using a field range and use `domain` instead:

```json
{
  "mark": {"type": "point"},
  "encoding": {
    "opacity": {
      "field": "x",
      "scale": {"domain": [false, true], "range": [1, 0.5]},
      "type": "nominal"
    }
  },
  "data": {"values": [{"x": false}, {"x": true}]}
}
```

However this may get messy as one will need to match the legend labels by hand, and more importantly this might not be an option if the domain is not known in advance.

